At House of Ruth,
a shelter for survivors of domestic violence and their children, a young boy
tries to sleep. Research shows that family violence places children at risk for
severe emotional problems, difficulties at school, and involvement in criminal
activity. As society continues to grapple with crime in general, and juvenile
crime in particular, House of Ruth is using Center funding to create a clinical
counseling program for children. To protect their privacy, the faces of
