</p>
<h2><a name="grants"></a><b>Grants Competitions:</b></h2>
<p>
<h3><b>Grants for Academic Initiatives</b></h3>
<p>
Over 230 applications were submitted for the Grants for Academic Initiatives competition, the first grant competition to be held at the newly-opened UICs in Yaroslavl and Novosibirsk.  The purpose of the competition is to support projects that propose to use the Internet as a tool to develop new approaches to teaching and research. Project proposals were received in the fields of education, science, medicine, and culture, and twenty projects will be awarded grants at each Center.<p>
<p><i>For press releases on the University Internet Centers, click <a 
href="http://www.soros.org/press.html#internet">here</a>. </i></p>

<p><i>For additional information on the University Internet Centers contact
H. Juergen Hess, Public Relations Director, Regional Internet Program,
Open Society Institute at <b><a href="mailto:jhess@sorosny.org">jhess@sorosny.org</a></b></i></p>

<p><i> </i>
