<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">                               
<html>                                                                          
<head>                                                                          
<meta name="description" content="Soros Foundations Network, Open Society Institute and National Foundations created and funded by George Soros">               
<meta name="keywords" content="Open Society Institute, George Soros, Soros Foundations, Recommended Reading">                                     
<title>Recommended Reading
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="FFFFFF" text="000000" link="93242B" alink="93242B" vlink="AD5F5B">    
<table cellpadding=6>                                                  
<tr>                                                                   
<td>                                                                   
<img align=middle src="/images/logo3.gif">                        
<td>                                                                   
<img align=middle src="/images/reading.gif" alt="Recommended Reading">         
</td>                                                                  
</tr>                                                                  
</table>                                                               
<i>
For those of you interested in knowing more about any of the
subjects or regions focused upon by the Soros Network, we have asked our
respective experts to share their reading lists:</i><p>
<a name="top"></a>
<center>
<b>
| <a href="reading.html#europe">Eastern Europe</a> |
<a href="reading.html#migration">Forced Migration</a> |
<a href="reading.html#burma">Burma</a> |
<a href="reading.html#drug">Drug Policy Issues</a> |
<a href="reading.html#death">Death and Dying</a> |
</b>
</center>
<br>
<a name="europe"></a>
<h2> 
<a href="gopher://gopher.soros.org/11/General_Info/Reading/EEuropean"><img align=middle src="/images/gopher.gif"> About Eastern Europe...</a>
</h2>

These materials were selected by various people at the <b><a
href="osiny.html">Open Society Institute in New York</a></b>, Anthony
Richter, assistant to the President selected the Central Asian reading,
while the Former Yugoslavia department contributed that region's
offerings. To ask about, or recommend, other reading, drop a note to:<p>

<Address>Anthony Richter, <a href="mailto:arichter@sorosny.org"><b>(arichter@sorosny.org)</b></a></address> 
<p><a href="#top"><img align=middle src="/images/go_up_bt.gif" alt="Top"></a>
<hr>
<a name="migration"></a>
<h2>
<a href="gopher://gopher.soros.org/11/General_Info/Reading/Migration"><img align=middle src="/images/gopher.gif"> About Forced Migration Issues...</a>
</h2>

These materials were selected by Arthur Helton, Director of the <b><a 
href="migrate.html"> Forced Migration Projects</a></b> and expert in the field of immigration law and migration related issues. For more information, send e-mail to:<p>

<Address><a href="mailto:refugee@sorosny.org"><b>(refugee@sorosny.org)</b></a></address> 
<p><a href="#top"><img align=middle src="/images/go_up_bt.gif" alt="Top"></a>
<hr>
<a name="burma"></a>
<h2>
<a href="gopher://gopher.soros.org/11/General_Info/Reading/Burma"><img align=middle src="/images/gopher.gif"> About Burma...</a>
</h2>
These materials were selected by Maureen Aung Thwin, Director of the 
<b><a href="burma.html"> Burma Project</a></b>. Maureen who has lived in India and the US among other places, she has been active in making people in the West aware of the situation in Burma and in helping to facilitate it's return to a more Open Society for a number of years. She can be reached at:<p>

<Address>Maureen Aung Thwin, <a href="mailto:maungthwin@sorosny.org"><b>(maungthwin@sorosny.org)</b></a></address> 
<p><a href="#top"><img align=middle src="/images/go_up_bt.gif" alt="Top"></a>
<hr>
<a name="drug"></a>
<h2>
<a href="http://www.lindesmith.org/lindesmith"><img align=middle src="/images/www.gif"> About Drug Policy Issues...</a>
</h2>

These materials were selected by Ethan Nadelmann, Director of <b><a 
href="http://www.lindesmith.org/lindesmith">The Lindesmith Center</a></b> and resident expert on legalization and other issues surrounding drug policy. Prior to establishing The Lindesmith Center, Ethan was a Professor at Princeton University.  He can be reached at:
<p>
<Address>Ethan Nadelmann, <a href="mailto:lindesmith@sorosny.org"><b>(lindesmith@sorosny.org)</b></a></address> 
<p><a href="#top"><img align=middle src="/images/go_up_bt.gif" alt="Top"></a>
<hr>
<a name="death"></a>
<h2>
<a href="death/pdiaread.html"><img align=middle src="/images/www.gif"> About Death and Dying...</a>
</h2>
These materials were selected by Dr. Kathleen Foley, Director of the <b><a
href="death.html">Project on Death in America</a></b>. Dr. Foley
is also attached to The Sloan Kettering Cancer Treatment Center and is a
pre-eminent authority on issues of terminal illness and pain management.
You can reach her through her assistant, Mary Callaway at:<p>

<Address>Mary Callaway, <a href="mailto:mcallaway@sorosny.org"><b>(mcallaway@sorosny.org)</b></a></address> 
<p><a href="#top"><img align=middle src="/images/go_up_bt.gif" alt="Top"></a>
<hr>                                                                            
