<html><head><title>                                                             
OSF Haiti - About the Country
</title></head>                                                                 
<body bgcolor="FFFFFF" text="000000" link="2A4572" alink="2A4572" vlink="587CA3">                                                                               
<table border=0 cellpadding=6>                                                  
<tr>                                                                            
<td><img src="/images/logo3.gif"></td>                                          
<td><h1>                                                                        
Open Society Foundation - Haiti<br>About the Country
</h1></td>
</table> 

Haiti's history is one of depletion. Cultivation has been allowed to use up rather than enrich the land. There is no infrastructure for the delivery of water, electricity, telecommunications, and other services. Where there is electricity, it is rarely operable for more than two to three hours a day. Piles of garbage line the streets of the poor and rich alike. The water is not drinkable, but people drink it of necessity. There are too few resources to adequately support a large and growing population. The country's drastic economic situation is exacerbated by the precocity of its institutions and the social and political instability linked to a tradition of state violence and repression.
<hr>
