<html><head><title>                                                             
Stefan Batory Foundation -  Poland - Country Background
</title></head>                                                                 
<body bgcolor="FFFFFF" text="000000" link="2A4572" alink="2A4572" vlink="587CA3">                                                                               
<table border=0 cellpadding=6>                                                  
<tr>                                                                            
<td><img src="/images/logo3.gif"></td>                                          
<td><h1>                                                                        
Stefan Batory Foundation -  Poland<br>Country Background
</h1></td>
</table> 

Public debate in Poland has been dominated recently by the words "democracy" and "market" 
while the idea of "civil society," which had been so influential in the political struggles of the 1970s and 
1980s, has fallen into disuse. Although "civil society" is no longer at the center of debate, it is only now, 
under democratic and free market conditions, that civil society has had the opportunity to flourish. The 
foundation supports the ventures of different organizations, associations, and nonformal groups, especially 
independent initiatives that unite people in a common cause, focus on culture and education, broaden 
knowledge about other nations, and help people in need or protect the environment. These initiatives 
empower individuals and groups to seek solutions to problems without waiting for government action.
<hr>
