<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">                               
<html><head><title>                                                             
SF Belarus - About the Country
</title></head>                                                                 
<body bgcolor="FFFFFF" text="000000" link="2A4572" alink="2A4572" vlink="587CA3">                                                                               
<table border=0 cellpadding=6>                                                  
<tr>                                                                            
<td><img src="/images/logo3.gif"></td>                                          
<td><h1>                                                                        
Belarusian Soros Foundation -<br>About the Country
</h1></td>
</table> 

Belarus began 1994 effectively bankrupt, and the economic situation did not improve greatly as the year progressed. The country is one of the last in Eastern Europe to resist privatization and a free market economy. Out of 375 enterprises that were to be privatized in 1994, only 145 had been privatized by October. Private companies made up only 10 percent of the country's economy. The most notable economic achievement in the past year was the liberalization of prices on a number of consumer goods.<p>

The administration and parliament have fought pitched battles for control of the government with some lawmakers conducting a hunger strike on the floor of the legislature and the president sending troops in to evict the protesters. Censorship of the media remains tight. The president banned independent newspapers from printing a report charging corruption in his administration.
<hr>
