<html><head><title>                                                             
OSI Macedonia - Country Background
</title></head>                                                                 
<body bgcolor="FFFFFF" text="000000" link="2A4572" alink="2A4572" vlink="587CA3">                                                                               
<table border=0 cellpadding=6>                                                  
<tr>                                                                            
<td><img src="/images/logo3.gif"></td>                                          
<td><h1>                                                                        
Open Society Institute - Macedonia<br>Country Background
</h1></td>
</table> 

The Open Society Institute-Macedonia was founded in October 1992 at a time when it had not yet received international recognition. During the difficult winter months of 1993, the foundation's programs and George Soros' assistance were the only source of hope for the citizens of Macedonia and the only evidence that the newly established independent state had not been completely forgotten by the international community and left to die slowly, somewhere at the edge of civilization and not far from the battlefields in Bosnia.
