<html><head><title>                                                             
SF Moldova - About the Country
</title></head>                                                                 
<body bgcolor="FFFFFF" text="000000" link="2A4572" alink="2A4572" vlink="587CA3">                                                                               
<table border=0 cellpadding=6>                                                  
<tr>                                                                            
<td><img src="/images/logo3.gif"></td>                                          
<td><h1>                                                                        
Soros Foundation - Moldova<br>About the Country
</h1></td>
</table> 

Moldova rose as an independent state from the ruins of the former Soviet Union in August 1991. Until then, Moldovan society was governed by rigid totalitarian laws, freedom of expression was nonexistent, access to information limited (especially regarding the West), travel aboard was restricted, and so-called nongovernmental organizations were controlled by the state. Resistance to the Soviet regime was stronger in the area of national problems than in the human rights area. After the disintegration of the Soviet Union and the emergence of Moldova as an independent state, the national problems being to a great extent solved, society proved to be unprepared for the danger that a quasi-totalitarian regime would be maintained on a local level. That danger still exists.
<hr>
