<H1>
Open Society News - Fall 1996</H1>
The Newsletter of the Open Society Institute<br>
<br>
Chairman George Soros<br>
President Aryeh Neier<br>
Executive vice president for finance Stewart Paperin<br>
Vice president for national foundations Deborah Harding<br>
Director of U.S. programs Gara LaMarche<br>
Director of regional programs Liz Lorant <br>
<br>
Open Society News <br>
editor Michael Vachon <br>
managing editor Iowaka Barber <br>
consulting editor Ari Korpivaara <br>
editorial assistant David Cote   <br>
intern Anne Gotwals<br>
<br>
Open Society News, published quarterly by the Office of Public Affairs of the
Open Society Institute-New York, reports on the activities and programs of the
Soros foundations network, created and funded by George Soros. At the heart of
this network are 24 autonomous foundations in Albania, Belarus, Bulgaria,
Bosnia &amp; Herzegovina, Croatia, the Czech Republic, Estonia, Georgia, Haiti,
Hungary, Kazakstan, Kyrgyzstan, Latvia, Lithuania, Macedonia, Moldova, Poland,
Romania, Russia, Slovakia, Slovenia, South Africa, Ukraine, and Yugoslavia, and
five information offices in Armenia, Azerbaijan, Mongolia, Tajikistan, and
Uzbekistan. In addition, the Institute operates programs concerned with
Southern Africa and Burma. All these organizations share the common mission of
fostering the development and maintenance of open society, supporting an array
of programs in the areas of educational, social, and legal reform. Together
with its Hungary-based sister organization, the Open Society
Institute-Budapest, the Open Society Institute-New York assists these
organizations in creating programs on common issues and by providing
administrative, financial, and technical support. The Open Society
Institute-New York also operates and/or supports a variety of programs that
focus on the United States, encouraging public debate and policy alternatives
in complex and often controversial fields. <br>
<br>
For additional information, see OSI-NY's web site at
&lt;http://www.soros.org&gt; or contact the Office of Public Affairs, Open
Society Institute, 888 Seventh Avenue, New York, NY 10106 USA; tel (212)
757-2323; fax (212) 245-3429; or e-mail &lt;osnews@sorosny.org&gt;.<br>
<br>
ISSN # 1706-9606<br>
Copyright (c) 1996 Open Society Institute<br>
